The paper focuses on distance measures for mixture distributions, which are commonly used in machine learning tasks such as generative models, domain adaptation, and clustering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also applies the proposed measure to GANs and domain adaptation, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper introduces a new distance measure, which involves optimization variables, making it relevant to the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses adversarial clustering, which is a topic studied in the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
